When you run a container we cleanup in a script being executed by conmon, `podman cleanup`.  Which could definitely cause this issue.
I thought that we had special cased the --rm to kill the container when not using the `-d` flag.
@mheon thoughts?

pkg/adapter/containers.go has:
```
		if err := r.Runtime.RemoveContainer(ctx, ctr, false, true); err != nil {
			if errors.Cause(err) == define.ErrNoSuchCtr {
				logrus.Warnf("Container %s does not exist: %v", ctr.ID(), err)
			} else {
				logrus.Errorf("Error removing container %s: %v", ctr.ID(), err)
			}
		}
```
Looks like we shouldbe handling this.
